name: Hubble's sharpest view of the Orion Nebula
description:
The image, taken by the Advanced Camera for Surveys (ACS) aboard NASA/ESA Hubble Space Telescope, represents the sharpest view ever taken of this region, called the Orion Nebula. 

Name:	Messier 42, Messier 43, Orion Nebula
Type:	Milky Way : Nebula : Type : Star Formation
Milky Way : Nebula : Appearance : Emission : H II Region
Distance:	1400 light years
Constellation:	Orion
Category:	Nebulae

3,629 editions for the known 3,629 planetary systems to date.
